### Sub-claims

| ID | Sub-claim | Status |
|---|---|---|
| G1.1 | [Concrete sub-claim — falsifiable as `confirmed` or `falsified` by one or more Purposes] | not started |
| G1.2 | [Next sub-claim] | not started |
| G1.3 | [...] | not started |

Sub-claim IDs (G1.1, G1.2, ...) are stable within the project and never
reused after retirement. Each Purpose's notebook references these IDs in
its Cycle goal (5th item). Each H row in `hypotheses.md` references
these IDs in its `target_sub_claim_id` column.

Sub-claim status legend:

- `not started`: no Purpose has attacked this sub-claim yet
- `in progress`: a Purpose is currently testing this sub-claim, or has
  produced partial evidence
- `confirmed`: at least one Purpose has produced a Primary YES on H's
  whose evidence settles the sub-claim
- `falsified`: at least one Purpose has produced a Fallback NO whose
  binding axis settles the sub-claim negatively
- `retired`: the sub-claim has been deliberately removed from the
  project's scope (the reason is logged in `decisions.md`)

Status updates are recorded in `decisions.md` at Purpose closure (in
the "Research-goal sub-claim progress update" section of each Purpose
entry).

