## Lifecycle

```
0. Decompose research goal into sub-claims (this README) — before any Purpose opens
1. Literature review → hypothesis portfolio (first H per Purpose, with target_sub_claim_id)
2. Per Purpose: write design hypothesis at open in decisions.md (which sub-claim does this Purpose attack?)
3. One notebook per Purpose; one or more H rounds tested inside it
4. At each H round: bug_review → robustness battery → experiment-review → per-H verdict → append per-H row to results.parquet
5. If a derived H serves the same Purpose: continue with the next H round inside the SAME notebook (the H inherits target_sub_claim_id from its parent unless explicitly overridden in hypotheses.md)
6. If the next investigation reflects a new Purpose: open the next notebook (the new Purpose's target_sub_claim_id is chosen from sub-claims still `not started` or `in progress`)
7. At Purpose close: update sub-claim status in decisions.md, write design hypothesis at close (CONFIRMED / FALSIFIED / PARTIAL)
8. Project complete when all sub-claims are `confirmed`, `falsified`, or `retired`
```

Detailed protocols live in the `quant-research` plugin's `references/` directory.
The four-layer model (Research goal / Design hypothesis / Purpose / Hypothesis)
that ties this README to per-H rows is in `references/research_goal_layer.md`.
